---
name: dataset-parallel-int
backends: [interpreter]
---

# Dataset — parallel runner parity (interpreter)

On the interpreter `runParallel()` uses cooperative concurrency
(same observable semantics as sequential for pure pipelines).

```scalascript
val data = Dataset.fromList(List.range(1, 51))  // 1..50

val seqResult = data.map(_ * 3).filter(_ % 9 == 0).runLocal().collect()
val parResult = data.map(_ * 3).filter(_ % 9 == 0).runParallel().collect()
println(seqResult.sorted.mkString(", "))
println(parResult.sorted.mkString(", "))
println(seqResult.sorted == parResult.sorted)

val seqSum = data.runLocal().reduce(_ + _)
val parSum = data.runParallel().reduce(_ + _)
println(seqSum)
println(seqSum == parSum)
```
